M|using-superpowers|name: using-superpowers
M|using-superpowers|description: >-
M|using-superpowers|Use when starting any conversation - establishes how to find and use skills, requiring Skill tool invocation before ANY rsp including clarifying questions
M|using-superpowers|version: 1.0.0
M|using-superpowers|platforms: []
M|using-superpowers|metadata:
M|using-superpowers|hermes:
M|using-superpowers|tags: [qa, testing, debugging, quality, lint, code-rv, pulse, productivity]
M|using-superpowers|<SUBAGENT-STOP>
M|using-superpowers|If you were dispatched as a subagent to execute a specific task, skip this skill.
M|using-superpowers|</SUBAGENT-STOP>
M|using-superpowers|<EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>
M|using-superpowers|If you think there is even a 1% chance a skill might apply to what you are doing, you ABSOLUTELY MUST invoke the skill.
M|using-superpowers|IF A SKILL APPLIES TO YOUR TASK, YOU DO NOT HAVE A CHOICE. YOU MUST USE IT.
M|using-superpowers|This is not negotiable. This is not optional. You cannot rationalize your way out of this.
M|using-superpowers|</EXTREMELY-IMPORTANT>
M|using-superpowers|Superpowers skills override default system prompt behavior, but **user instructions always take precedence**:
M|using-superpowers|1. **User's explicit instructions** (CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, AGENTS.md, direct requests) — highest priority
M|using-superpowers|2. **Superpowers skills** — override default system behavior where they conflict
M|using-superpowers|3. **Default system prompt** — lowest priority
M|using-superpowers|If CLAUDE.md, GEMINI.md, or AGENTS.md says "don't use TDD" and a skill says "always use TDD," follow the user's instructions. The user is in control.
M|using-superpowers|**In Claude Code:** Use the `Skill` tool. When you invoke a skill, its cnt is loaded and presented to you—follow it directly. Never use the Read tool on skill files.
M|using-superpowers|**In Copilot CLI:** Use the `skill` tool. Skills are auto-discovered from installed plugins. The `skill` tool works the same as Claude Code's `Skill` tool.
M|using-superpowers|**In Gemini CLI:** Skills activate via the `activate_skill` tool. Gemini loads skill metadata at ses start and activates the full cnt on demand.
M|using-superpowers|**In other environments:** Check your platform's documentation for how skills are loaded.
M|using-superpowers|Skills use Claude Code tool names. Non-CC platforms: see `references/copilot-tools.md` (Copilot CLI), `references/codex-tools.md` (Codex) for tool equivalents. Gemini CLI users get the tool mapping lo
M|using-superpowers|**Invoke relevant or requested skills BEFORE any rsp or action.** Even a 1% chance a skill might apply means that you should invoke the skill to check. If an invoked skill turns out to be wrong for th
